enum MessageIdentifier::Type
 

Enumerator:
InPlmnOperatorAssociationsRange  To be allocated by PLMN operator associations. If a Message Identifier from this range is in the "search list", the ME shall attempt to receive such CBS message. This version of GSM 03.41 does not prohibit networks from using Message Identifiers in the range 0000 - 03E7 (hex) for Cell Broadcast Data Download to the SIM.
LcsEOtdAssistanceDataMessage  LCS CBS Message Identifier for E-OTD Assistance Data message.
LcsDGpsCorrectionDataMessage  LCS CBS Message Identifier for DGPS Correction Data message.
LcsGpsEphemerisAndClockCorrectionDataMessage  LCS CBS Message Identifier for GPS Ephemeris and Clock Correction Data message.
LcsGpsAlmanacAndOtherDataMessage  LCS CBS Message Identifier for GPS Almanac and Other Data message.
InUnsecureCellBroadcastDataDownloadRange  Networks shall only use Message Identifiers from this range for Cell Broadcast Data Download in "clear" (i.e. unsecured) to the SIM (see GSM 11.14). If a message Identifier from this range is in the "search list", the ME shall attempt to receive this CBS message.
InSecureCellBroadcastDataDownloadRange  Networks shall only use Message Identifiers from this range for Cell Broadcast Data Download secured according to GSM 03.48 [15] to the SIM (see GSM 11.14). If a message Identifier from this range is in the "search list", the ME shall attempt to receive this CBS message.
InPlmnOperatorSpecificRange  PLMN operator specific range. The type of information provided by PLMN operators using these Message Identifiers is not guaranteed to be the same across different PLMNs. If a Message Identifier from this range is in the "search list", the ME shall attempt to receive this CBS message.
InPlmnOperatorSpecificForFutureVersionsRange  Intended for standardization in future versions of GSM 03.41. These values shall not be transmitted by networks that are compliant to this version of GSM 03.41. If a Message Identifier from this range is in the "search list", the ME shall attempt to receive this CBS message.
InReservedForFutureVersionsRange  Intended for standardization or PLMN operator specific range in future versions of GSM 03.41. These values shall not be transmitted by networks that are compliant to this version of GSM 03.41. If a Message Identifier from this range is in the "search list", the ME shall attempt to receive this CBS message.
InvalidType  Reserved, and should not be used for new services, as this value is used on the SIM to indicate that no Message Identifier is stored in those two octets of the SIM. If this Message Identifier is in the "search list", the ME shall attempt to receive this CBS message.
